Ask HN: How do you talk to competitors?
text:
Does anyone have any best practices for talking to competitors? My company just launched a new product and a lot of players in this space are reaching out to learn more about what we're building.

I see pros and cons to speaking with competitors.

Pros: shared learnings, potential partnerships.

Cons: blatant copying, stifled market opportunity.

Random Emails Gone from Gmail
text:
One of my workflow within gmail is to use it as searchable history of conversations/receipts/confirmations emails.

While I was printing out all the confirmation for upcoming holiday, I needed to get the confirmation of car rental.

Searched in gmail search - no email confirmation returned, seemed strange as I remember that I check it in December. Checked credit card history - it was payed although payment details did not had rental company name nor reservation confirmation id. - searched gmail mails around payment time - no match. - searched browser history - found links to gmail url with confirmation id around December, gmail url does not opens the email but inbox.

With confirmation id, I went through one-by-one on rental company to finally get the voucher by confirmation id and email.

This is the second time where email was simply gone from gmail - is it me (I'm loosing the trust for myself) or more then gmail issue?
